article.headline: George Mason 89, Delaware 63
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- Ryan Pearson scored 24 points and Mike Morrison added 17 as George Mason routed Delaware 89-63 on Wednesday night. Pearson added 10 rebounds, four steals and two blocked shots for the Patriots (14-5, 6-1 Colonial Athletic Conference) and Byron Allen chipped in 12 points. Devon Sadler led the Blue Hens (7-10, 3-4) with 21 points. Josh Brinkley added 14 before fouling out and Jamelle Hagins scored 10. George Mason led by 15 at intermission, but the Blue Hens got to within 51-42 on a Hagins dunk early in the second half. Vaughn Gray responded with a 3-pointer for George Mason, igniting a 15-4 run that put the Patriots ahead by 20 with just over 11 minutes left in the game. George Mason led by as many as 29 late in the game.
